    <text type="petition">
        <body>            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01064.001.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">
                <dateline><date when="1862-07-18">July 18</date>.</dateline>
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <ab><persName>Eliza V. Hall</persName>. I know <persName>William Hall</persName> he is my brother He belonged to <persName>Eliza V. Griffith</persName>. He has been here ever since <date when="1862-02">February last</date>. He was put in jail by mistress order. He was put in jail because he ran away. He was turned out two weeks after I dont know that his mistress knew where he was. She made no claim. He was in <placeName>Alexandria</placeName> part of the time—here every week—</ab>
                    <ab>has been publicly about streets since that time</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <ab><persName>Benedict <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#jc">Milton</unclear></persName>—never saw man until today. dont know his name I <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#jc">gave</unclear> this list from the book.</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01064.003.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab>runaway slave—<date when="1862-02-05">Feby 5, 1862</date> <persName>Wm Hall</persName> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#jc">committed</unclear> by <persName>F. I. Murphey</persName> discharged <date when="1862-02-15">15 Feby last</date> by <persName>F. I. Murphey</persName> to <persName>F. <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#el">Wilton</unclear></persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <ab>4</ab>
                    <ab><persName>Eliza V. Griffith</persName>'s servant <persName>William Hall</persName></ab>
                    <ab><date when="1862-07-18">July 18, 1862</date></ab>
                </div2>
            </div1>            
        </body>
    </text>
